cs.CL, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on natural language understanding and semantic parsing, which are core topics in this sub-category.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper specifically deals with the application of the proposed approach to a house service robot, making it highly relevant to this sub-category.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of neural networks and attention mechanisms in the proposed approach falls under the scope of this sub-category.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper's focus on the use of a multi-layer LSTM neural network for modeling robot command interaction makes it relevant to this sub-category.
5. cs.SD (Sound) - Although less likely, this sub-category deals with sound processing and analysis, which is relevant to the vocal interface used in the paper's approach.
